{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6429718a-091b-48e2-842e-67d6c12d8f9c","content":"Here's what I've created and what you need to do:\n\n## Created: `.github/workflows/publish.yml`\n\nThis workflow triggers on version tags (`v*`), packs your library, obtains an OIDC token, and pushes to nuget.org — no API key stored anywhere.\n\n## You still need to do two things:\n\n### 1. Configure nuget.org (Trusted Publisher)\n\nGo to [nuget.org](https://www.nuget.org) → your account → **Manage Packages** → select/register your package → **Trusted Publishers** and add:\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Repository owner | `myorg` |\n| Repository name | `mylib` |\n| Workflow file | `publish.yml` |\n| Environment | `nuget.org` |\n\n### 2. Create the GitHub environment\n\nIn your repo → **Settings → Environments** → create an environment named **`nuget.org`**. Optionally add protection rules (required reviewers, tag restrictions, etc.).\n\n## To publish a release:\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe workflow will build, pack, and push using OIDC — no secrets required.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1265ed8a-19a3-4ea2-bcf3-28d311be5c0e","outputTokens":294,"requestId":"FE1F:41C1F:14FF9B3:17502A5:6A066EB2"},"id":"3f83d568-7f7a-4f51-9aa7-6a4420e02bc6","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:54:19.711Z","parentId":"c3eb6d20-8330-4a92-aaae-a4fe6ad59ce5"}
